<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-7897] Camel consumes &amp; discards activemq messages after suspension</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-7897</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When used with a PooledConnectionFactory, a Camel Route that consumes via JMS from an ActiveMQ endpoint will read one extra message and simply discard it &lt;b&gt;after&lt;/b&gt; it has completed suspension, if that message is sent within a second of suspension being completed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See attached test case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as I can tell this is because nothing interrupts the taskExecutor on DefaultMessageListenerContainer when a route is suspended.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected behaviour - once a route is suspended, any messages sent to the queue from which it consumes should remain on that queue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;All&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
