                            <comment id="14163787" author="mahoney" created="Wed, 8 Oct 2014 17:09:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See attached JUnit test and pom specifying its dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14163791" author="mahoney" created="Wed, 8 Oct 2014 17:09:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you use the ActiveMQConnectionFactory directly, without the wrapping PooledConnectionFactory, the test will pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14322044" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 15 Feb 2015 16:21:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See the note about pooled consumers and prefect&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://activemq.apache.org/what-is-the-prefetch-limit-for.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://activemq.apache.org/what-is-the-prefetch-limit-for.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14322059" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 15 Feb 2015 16:35:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is always a window of opportunity that the jms consumer pickup new messages while suspending.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can set acceptMessagesWhileStopping=true and process the messages instead of rejecting them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then when the suspending is complete new messages stats on the queue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
